flowRoot.flowPara: Proteopathogen2.0, a database and web tool to store and display proteomics identification results in the MzIdentML standard format

Proteopathogen2.0 is a database-backed web application on shotgun Proteomics experiments addressed at the study of Candida albicans and other fungal pathogens and their interaction with the host. It follows the idea first implemented in the original version of Proteopathogen, proteopathogen.dacya.ucm.es (Vialas et al. 2009, Proteomics)
